  "name": "Shroud of Vermin",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/skills/green_23.jpg",
  "sort": 0,
  "flags": {},
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 9th level, <em>swarms</em> no longer see you as prey. You can walk among <em>swarms</em> without <em>fear</em> of being harmed by them at all, and by taking a <em>standard action</em> to mentally <em>command</em> a <em>swarm</em> in which you stand, you can direct that <em>swarm’s</em> attacks and movements as long as you have more <em>Hit Dice</em> than the <em>swarm</em>. Even when you aren’t standing amid a <em>swarm</em>, your body crawls with <em>vermin</em>, and their chitinous bodies increase your <em>natural armor bonus</em> by +1. At 11th level, this bonus increases to +2, and at 17th level it increases to +3.</p>"
    },
